SUMMARY:Deadline: Medialab Matadero: Situated Research Residencies 2027 (Ma
 drid)
DESCRIPTION:Medialab Matadero in Madrid selects three projects for a resear
 ch and creation residency bringing together contemporary art\, design\, sc
 ience\, technology and society\, welcoming critical\, experimental and col
 laborative work. Each project must connect clearly with one or more themes
  from Medialab's recent programs: LAB 1 Sentient Media\, LAB 2 The Metabol
 ic Sublime\, LAB 3 Synthetic Minds\, LAB 4 Weird Futures and LAB 5 The Mec
 hanics of Truth. Open to individuals and collectives from any discipline (
 design\, art\, architecture\, film\, journalism\, digital media\, environm
 ental science\, philosophy\, engineering\, programming\, activism and more
 ). SUPPORT: EUR 10\,000 per project (before taxes)\, individual workspace\
 , access to the Fablab and technical materials\, curatorial team guidance\
 , and logistical and financial support for public activities\; proposals m
 ust include public engagement plans and produce documentation. RESIDENCY: 
 January to July 2027\, in person in Madrid. DEADLINE: 27 September 2026. N
 o application fee.\n\nOrganisation: Medialab Matadero\nLocation: Madrid\, 
 Spain. In-person residency\; open internationally to individuals and colle
 ctives.\nAward: EUR 10\,000 per project (before taxes) for three selected 
 projects\, plus individual workspace\, Fablab and technical materials\, cu
 ratorial guidance\, and logistical and financial support for public activi
 ties. No application fee.\nDuration: January to July 2027\; cannot be carr
 ied out remotely\, with extended stays in Madrid recommended especially Ma
 rch to June. Live online Q&A on 8 September 2026\, 6pm CEST.\n\nMore: http
 s://www.medialab-matadero.es/en/announcements/situated-research-2027?utm_s
 ource=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.medialab-matadero.es/en/announcements/situated-research-202
 7?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Madrid\, Spain. In-person residency\; open internationally to indi
 viduals and collectives.
